---
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="description" content="About — inceptionalism.xyz" />
    <title>About — inceptionalism.xyz</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Nav />
    <main>
      <section class="intro">
        <p>
          AI artist working on Ethereum since 2021. The practice started with GANs and hasn't settled —
          Valley Girls, Two Winters, Drifters, MINING_PROTOCOL, We. Each piece finds its own form.
          Technology has to earn its place in the concept or it doesn't belong.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="selected-work">
        <h2>Selected work</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/work/on-chain">MINING_PROTOCOL</a></li>
          <li><a href="/work/on-chain">We</a></li>
          <li><a href="/work/valley-girls">Valley Girls</a></li>
          <li><a href="/work/two-winters">Two Winters</a></li>
          <li><a href="/work/drifters">Drifters</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="statement">
        <h2>Statement</h2>
        <p>
          The work started with a simple observation: AI can only reflect what it was trained on. Which
          means it reflects us. Valley Girls was a snapshot of that reflection at a specific moment —
          before the uncanny valley closed. The model kept returning beautiful white faces. Getting a
          representative set required fighting it. That fight was the concept made technical.
        </p>
        <p>
          Two Winters inverted the thing. A Finnish photographer named popsto shot real aurora timelapses
          in West Lapland. I made the foreground figures — AI-generated, frame by frame. The sky, usually
          where you put the dream, is real. The ground, usually where you put reality, is AI. We handed
          the ethereal to photography and gave the earth to the machine.
        </p>
        <p>
          MINING_PROTOCOL is a self-contained HTML file that mines Monero while you view it. We runs real
          inference on a million Reddit confessions. Those pieces required real computation because the
          concept demanded it — not because every piece does.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="colophon">
        <p class="muted">
          inceptionalism.xyz · rightonricky.eth · Ethereum mainnet · Foundation · Transient Labs
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  section + section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .intro p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: #666;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .selected-work ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .selected-work a {
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .statement p {
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .statement p + p {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .colophon {
    border-top: 1px solid #e8e8e8;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
  }
</style>
